Document: SpriteFrames
Path: godot/classes/class_spriteframes.rst
Summary: Provides methods for managing animations and frames within a SpriteFrames resource, including adding, removing, modifying, and querying animation and frame properties.

Method: add_animation(anim: StringName)
Adds a new animation to the library.

Method: add_frame(anim: StringName, texture: Texture2D, duration: float = 1.0, at_position: int = -1)
Adds a frame to the specified animation. If at_position is -1, the frame is added to the end. duration specifies the relative duration.

Method: clear(anim: StringName)
Removes all frames from the specified animation.

Method: clear_all()
Removes all animations. An empty "default" animation will be created.

Method: duplicate_animation(anim_from: StringName, anim_to: StringName)
Duplicates an existing animation to a new animation name. Fails if the target animation name already exists or the source animation does not exist.

Method: get_animation_loop(anim: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the animation is configured to loop, false otherwise.

Method: get_animation_names() → PackedStringArray
Returns an array containing the names of all animations, sorted alphabetically.

Method: get_animation_speed(anim: StringName) → float
Returns the speed of the specified animation in frames per second.

Method: get_frame_count(anim: StringName) → int
Returns the number of frames in the specified animation.

Method: get_frame_duration(anim: StringName, idx: int) → float
Returns the relative duration of a specific frame within an animation. The absolute duration in seconds can be calculated using the formula: absolute_duration = relative_duration / (animation_fps * abs(playing_speed)).

Method: get_frame_texture(anim: StringName, idx: int) → Texture2D
Returns the texture of a specific frame within an animation.

Method: has_animation(anim: StringName) → bool
Returns true if an animation with the given name exists.

Method: remove_animation(anim: StringName)
Removes the specified animation.

Method: remove_frame(anim: StringName, idx: int)
Removes a specific frame from an animation.

Method: rename_animation(anim: StringName, newname: StringName)
Changes the name of an existing animation.

Method: set_animation_loop(anim: StringName, loop: bool)
Sets whether the specified animation should loop when it finishes playing.

Method: set_animation_speed(anim: StringName, fps: float)
Sets the speed of the specified animation in frames per second.

Method: set_frame(anim: StringName, idx: int, texture: Texture2D, duration: float = 1.0)
Sets the texture and relative duration for a specific frame within an animation.